'''Crissy Ahmann-Leighton''' (born 20 May 1970) is an [[United States|American]] [[Swimming (sport)|swimmer]] and olympic champion. She competed at the [[1992 Olympic Games]] in [[Barcelona]], where she received a gold medal in ''4 &times; 100 m [[medley swimming|medley]] relay'', a gold medal in ''4 &times; 100 m [[freestyle (swimming)|freestyle]] relay'', and a silver medal in ''100 m [[butterfly stroke|butterfly]]''.<ref name=db-olymp-1992SWI>[http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=23&sp=SWI "1992 Olympics &ndash; Barcelona, Spain &ndash; Swimming"] &ndash; ''databaseOlympics.com''<small> (Retrieved on 10 September 2008)</small></ref> 

